I/O for data frames and typed CSVs

Source: R/io.R
write_tcsv.Rd

I/O for data frames and typed CSVs

Usage

write_tcsv(dt, fout, sep = ",")

read_tcsv(fin, sep = ",")

Arguments

dt

A data frame to be written to file.

fout

Output file path.

sep

Character. The delimiter used for the typed CSV. Defaults to comma (,).

fin

Path to a typed CSV to be read in.

Examples

(d = data.frame(
    A_int = 1L:6L,
    A_dbl = seq(0, 1, length=6),
    A_cpl = (1:6) + 1i,
    A_lgl = rep(c(T,F), 3),
    A_fct = as.factor(head(LETTERS)),
    A_chr = head(LETTERS),
    A_utf8 = strsplit("你好我是大雄", "")[[1]])
)
